articles.title: NYC-area train derailment hurts no one, snarls morning rush
articles.description: The NJ Transit derailment happened in Perth Amboy around 12:20 a.m. as North Jersey Coast Line Train 3292 headed to New York's Penn Station from Long Branch, agency spokesperson Jim Smith said. The cars remained upright, and none of the seven passengers on board or the crew were injured, Smith said.
